Where are you going?

15:59.592 --> 16:02.193
Probably better you don't know.

16:02.195 --> 16:04.429
Are you gonna tell
Javier the truth?

16:04.431 --> 16:07.065
Are you kidding?
- He'll never speak to me again.

16:07.067 --> 16:09.500
So, how you gonna stop him?

16:09.502 --> 16:10.335
I don't know.

16:10.337 --> 16:11.569
I'll figure it out
when I get there.

16:11.571 --> 16:14.906
- You always do.
- Not always.

16:17.610 --> 16:20.445
♪ Shot your cannonball, lover ♪

16:20.447 --> 16:22.613
♪ Yeah, you got me
in the heart ♪

16:22.615 --> 16:25.083
♪ We'll go riding up
and down the elevators ♪

16:25.085 --> 16:29.487
♪ Baby, kiss me all over until
the only thing I see is stars ♪

16:29.489 --> 16:32.423
♪ Why don't you love me? ♪

16:32.425 --> 16:35.393
♪ Why do you run? ♪

16:35.395 --> 16:37.628
♪ Why won't you love me? ♪

16:37.630 --> 16:38.963
♪ I'm going to L.A., baby ♪

16:38.965 --> 16:40.932
♪ I'm gonna hunt you down ♪

16:40.934 --> 16:42.233
♪ I'm gonna make you mine ♪

16:42.235 --> 16:44.168
Man: Welcome to
- The Atlantic Wilmington.

16:44.170 --> 16:44.702
Thanks.

16:44.704 --> 16:46.371
Wait, I have to finish
my makeup.

16:46.373 --> 16:47.405
Oh, of course, ma'am.

16:47.407 --> 16:49.407
♪ Ooh, gonna make you mine ♪

16:49.409 --> 16:51.576
♪ Ooh, gonna make you mine ♪

16:51.578 --> 16:54.345
Could you just give
me a second?

16:54.347 --> 16:57.081
Oh, of course.

16:57.083 --> 16:59.684
♪ I don't wanna be your friend ♪

16:59.686 --> 17:02.286
♪ I just wanna be your girl ♪

17:02.288 --> 17:04.689
♪ I got a fever and
it's runnin' so high ♪

17:04.691 --> 17:08.493
♪ If I never get to see you
again, I think I'm gonna die ♪

17:08.495 --> 17:12.363
♪ Why don't you love me? ♪

17:12.365 --> 17:14.499
♪ Why do you run? ♪

17:14.501 --> 17:16.100
♪ I'm going to L.A., baby ♪

17:16.102 --> 17:17.502
♪ I'm gonna hunt you down ♪

17:17.504 --> 17:19.270
Welcome to
The Atlantic Wilmington.

17:19.272 --> 17:20.471
Are you checking in with us?

17:20.473 --> 17:22.573
Sort of.
- I'm here to meet my husband.

17:22.575 --> 17:23.508
He already checked in,

17:23.510 --> 17:25.109
but I'm not sure
which room he's in.

17:25.111 --> 17:26.344
I can look that up for you.

17:26.346 --> 17:28.446
What name is
the reservation under?

17:28.448 --> 17:29.781
Pereira.

17:29.783 --> 17:31.549
Do you mind spelling that?

17:31.551 --> 17:32.095
P-e-r...

17:36.589 --> 17:38.923
e...

17:40.560 --> 17:43.327
r-i-a.

17:43.329 --> 17:44.128
Hmm.

17:44.130 --> 17:46.197
I don't have anyone here
by that name.

17:46.199 --> 17:48.032
Are you sure
that's how you spell it?

17:48.034 --> 17:51.269
We just got married.
I'm still learning it.

17:51.271 --> 17:52.070
[ Chuckles ]

17:52.072 --> 17:53.371
Do you know what?
Try Santino.

17:53.373 --> 17:56.574
Santino Pereira, or
is this a new last name?

17:56.576 --> 18:02.146
Can you... can you try it as
a first name and a last name?

18:02.148 --> 18:03.214
I'm confused.

18:03.216 --> 18:06.951
Don't be.
Just type it in.

18:08.721 --> 18:12.557
There are no first or last name
Santinos or Pereiras.

18:12.559 --> 18:16.194
If you'll excuse me, I have
to check in the next guests.

18:16.196 --> 18:18.196
Look, I'm sorry.
Here's the deal.

18:18.198 --> 18:20.064
My husband and I
have this thing

18:20.066 --> 18:22.033
where every year
on our anniversary,

18:22.035 --> 18:24.702
he checks into a hotel
under a different name,

18:24.704 --> 18:27.605
and then I knock on his door
and pretend

18:27.607 --> 18:30.741
like I'm another guest
staying at the hotel

18:30.743 --> 18:34.512
who's been locked out
of her room.

18:34.514 --> 18:36.781
Why?

18:36.783 --> 18:38.683
You know, like role playing.

18:38.685 --> 18:41.986
Oh.

18:41.988 --> 18:44.455
Fun.
[ Chuckles ]

18:44.457 --> 18:46.124
Very.
Only this year,

18:46.126 --> 18:48.359
I've clearly
forgotten the name.

18:48.361 --> 18:49.794
Well, uh, shoot
some more names at me.

18:49.796 --> 18:51.496
Let's see
if we can find a match.

18:51.498 --> 18:52.997
Amazing.
Thank you.

18:52.999 --> 18:55.900
Uh, try Diaz.

18:59.339 --> 19:01.672
I have a Mr. Diaz
in room 434.

19:01.674 --> 19:04.475
Great.
Can you make me a key?

19:04.477 --> 19:06.344
A key?

19:06.346 --> 19:07.346
I thought the fantasy was

19:07.347 --> 19:09.380
that you're a guest
in some other room?

19:09.382 --> 19:12.049
That's right.
- Thank you for reminding me.

19:12.051 --> 19:14.519
Room 434?

19:14.521 --> 19:15.586
434.

19:15.588 --> 19:17.889
[ Elevator dings ]

19:23.730 --> 19:26.664
[ Doorbell rings ]

19:29.636 --> 19:30.568
Diaz: Can I help you?

19:30.570 --> 19:32.436
I'm sorry.
- I must have the wrong room.

19:32.438 --> 19:34.205
Well, who are you looking for?

19:34.207 --> 19:34.772
Mr. Diaz.

19:34.774 --> 19:37.375
Well, that's me.
I-I'm Mr. Diaz.

19:37.377 --> 19:42.013
I'm sorry. I'm looking
for a different Mr. Diaz.

19:46.286 --> 19:47.952
[ Sighs ]

19:52.058 --> 19:53.457
[ Doorbells ringing ]

19:53.459 --> 19:56.060
♪ Mmmmm ♪

19:56.896 --> 19:59.463
- You're not room service.
- No.

19:59.465 --> 20:03.201
Where's the fucking
room service?

20:03.203 --> 20:04.435
♪ Heeeey ♪

20:04.437 --> 20:05.336
[ Elevator dings ]

20:05.338 --> 20:08.239
♪ I ain't lookin' for love ♪

20:08.241 --> 20:09.840
♪ Heeey ♪

20:09.842 --> 20:12.777
♪ I don't wanna ride today ♪

20:12.779 --> 20:13.911
♪ Heeey ♪

20:13.913 --> 20:15.780
♪ I'm tired of bein' stung ♪

20:15.782 --> 20:17.281
[ Doorbell rings ]

20:17.283 --> 20:19.217
♪ Got something
that I can't control ♪

20:19.219 --> 20:20.484
- Hi.
- Hi.

20:20.486 --> 20:21.519
[ Doorbells ringing ]

20:21.521 --> 20:24.322
♪ I got the taste on my lips
and I want some more ♪

20:24.324 --> 20:26.624
♪ Want some more,
want some more ♪

20:26.626 --> 20:27.925
♪ Come on ♪
- ♪ Hey, hey ♪

20:27.927 --> 20:29.760
- ♪ Feels so good ♪
- ♪ Hey, hey ♪

20:29.762 --> 20:32.496
- ♪ Feels so good ♪
- ♪ Hey, hey ♪

20:32.498 --> 20:34.332
♪ Feels so good ♪

20:34.334 --> 20:35.666
♪ Oooh ♪

20:35.668 --> 20:38.302
♪ What you want ♪

20:56.656 --> 20:58.489
What are you doing here?

21:01.461 --> 21:03.594
I got Jacob.

21:10.136 --> 21:12.637
[ Telephone rings ]

21:12.639 --> 21:14.605
Atlantic.

21:16.743 --> 21:19.043
I called for my car...
room 917.

21:19.045 --> 21:21.145
- On its way, sir.
- Thank you.

21:21.147 --> 21:24.015
You are not coming with me.
I have work to do.

21:24.017 --> 21:26.951
- I'm just standing here.
- Okay.

21:33.559 --> 21:34.358
Full custody?

21:34.360 --> 21:37.662
Yes.
- Sean has some visitation.

21:37.664 --> 21:39.697
That's good.

21:39.699 --> 21:41.165
How did this happen?

21:41.167 --> 21:45.002
I guess custody usually
goes to the mother, so...

21:45.004 --> 21:45.803
Even you?

21:45.805 --> 21:48.306
I know.
[ Chuckles ]

21:49.242 --> 21:51.409
Congratulations.

21:51.411 --> 21:52.443
Come with me.

21:52.445 --> 21:54.145
- No.
- We're a good team.

21:54.147 --> 21:56.414
We are not a good team.

21:59.986 --> 22:01.152
New car?

22:01.154 --> 22:04.588
Yeah. It's...
- It's the same, but black.

22:04.590 --> 22:06.524
Like my hair.

22:06.526 --> 22:07.625
What?

22:07.627 --> 22:08.492
This is the red wig.

22:08.494 --> 22:11.295
The one you told me
never to wear again.

22:11.297 --> 22:12.163
I dyed it black.

22:12.165 --> 22:16.233
I told you I wouldn't throw away
an $8,000 wig.

22:16.235 --> 22:18.069
You did.

22:20.406 --> 22:21.505
[ Sighs ]

22:21.507 --> 22:22.406
Where are you going?

22:22.408 --> 22:24.075
Somewhere you're not going.

22:24.077 --> 22:26.444
Look, I didn't mean to say
we're separate people.

22:26.446 --> 22:27.678
We're not.
I need you.

22:27.680 --> 22:28.479
No, you don't.

22:28.481 --> 22:30.281
Yes, I do, and Jacob needs you
and you need us.

22:30.283 --> 22:31.615
- I'm happy for you.
- Then...

22:31.617 --> 22:34.385
Please.
Go and be happy.

22:40.727 --> 22:44.362
Can I get my car, please?

22:55.708 --> 22:56.707
[ Door opens ]

22:56.709 --> 22:59.110
I thought you were done
killing people.
I told you to go.

22:59.112 --> 23:00.311
I thought you were done
with this.

23:00.313 --> 23:01.545
When did I say that?
I never said that.

23:01.547 --> 23:03.547
Whoever this person is, maybe
they don't deserve to die.

23:03.549 --> 23:05.750
- They do deserve to die.
- How do you know that?

23:05.752 --> 23:07.518
You don't ask
for their stories anymore.

23:07.520 --> 23:10.554
They... they volunteer
their information.

23:10.556 --> 23:11.322
Now, Letty...

23:11.324 --> 23:14.225
Letty.
Please.

23:14.227 --> 23:16.360
Go away.

23:16.362 --> 23:19.597
[ Door opens and closes ]

23:35.615 --> 23:37.615
♪ This city was never mine ♪

23:37.617 --> 23:40.284
I stopped drinking,
- So you should stop killing.

23:40.286 --> 23:41.819
You did not stop drinking.

23:41.821 --> 23:42.720
I only drink wine.

23:42.722 --> 23:45.589
That equals being sober
for anybody else.

23:45.591 --> 23:47.591
We need to talk
about the chef thing.

23:47.593 --> 23:48.559
What about the chef thing?

23:48.561 --> 23:50.828
I mean, you can actually cook
really well.

23:50.830 --> 23:51.829
Professionally well.

23:51.831 --> 23:55.566
♪ So they say
I've lost my mind ♪

23:55.568 --> 23:57.868
Can you fit in this?

23:57.870 --> 24:00.271
Can I fit in that?
No.

24:00.273 --> 24:02.907
- Try.
- I'm not trying.

24:02.909 --> 24:05.409
You're not putting a body
in there?

24:05.411 --> 24:06.710
I am.

24:06.712 --> 24:08.612
Maybe yours.

24:08.614 --> 24:10.514
You could be a real chef.

24:10.516 --> 24:12.416
Get in.

24:12.418 --> 24:16.353
♪ But I love the way ♪

24:16.355 --> 24:21.325
♪ You put me in the jade house ♪

24:21.327 --> 24:27.431
♪ No one believes you now ♪

24:27.433 --> 24:31.502
♪ But I love the way ♪

24:31.504 --> 24:36.474
♪ You put me in the jade house ♪

24:40.780 --> 24:43.647
♪ Was falling over again ♪

24:43.649 --> 24:44.548
[ Sighs ]

24:44.550 --> 24:45.850
They're all the same.

24:45.852 --> 24:47.918
Just get the powdered ones.

24:47.920 --> 24:50.254
I don't like the powdered ones.

24:50.256 --> 24:51.322
There is a difference.

24:51.324 --> 24:53.491
I don't know what to tell you.

24:53.493 --> 24:56.393
[ Scanner beeps ]

24:56.395 --> 25:02.900
♪ Do you require
my attire? ♪

25:02.902 --> 25:05.436
[ Scanner beeping ]

25:05.438 --> 25:09.573
♪ I want you to ♪

25:10.910 --> 25:16.747
♪ No one believes you now ♪

25:16.749 --> 25:18.482
You are not stealing that.

25:18.484 --> 25:19.517
♪ But I love the way ♪

25:19.519 --> 25:21.285
There's no one even here yet.

25:21.287 --> 25:21.852
I am here.

25:21.854 --> 25:26.056
♪ You put me in the jade house ♪

25:35.835 --> 25:39.103
Will you look at me?

25:51.517 --> 25:53.551
Stop.

26:02.862 --> 26:04.895
[ Gun clicks ]

26:04.897 --> 26:06.597
No.

26:08.968 --> 26:10.434
Stop.

26:10.436 --> 26:11.468
No.

26:11.470 --> 26:13.237
Stop it.

26:13.239 --> 26:14.371
I said stop it.

26:14.373 --> 26:18.309
I am not
your goddamn boyfriend.

26:18.311 --> 26:20.511
I know.

26:58.384 --> 27:00.384
Are you mad at me?

27:00.386 --> 27:01.986
Stop it.

27:01.988 --> 27:03.754
You seem really angry.

27:03.756 --> 27:06.824
I am very angry.

27:06.826 --> 27:09.193
Turn around.

27:12.632 --> 27:15.499
[ Panting ]

27:28.514 --> 27:32.683
[ Moaning ]

28:16.996 --> 28:18.829
Who was better?

28:18.831 --> 28:21.031
What?

28:21.033 --> 28:23.767
Who... you better?
Me or Sean?

28:25.871 --> 28:27.905
We're not a good team.

28:34.046 --> 28:36.714
Go.
I have to work.

28:36.716 --> 28:37.848
Please don't.

28:37.850 --> 28:39.950
Go.

28:39.952 --> 28:42.586
Go!

28:42.588 --> 28:46.590
Fine. Do it.

28:46.592 --> 28:47.725
Go kill that person

28:47.727 --> 28:51.495
and live with yourself
by yourself.

28:54.700 --> 28:57.401
[ Door slams ]

29:13.519 --> 29:15.619
[ Knock on door ]

29:18.557 --> 29:20.457
Hi, Estelle.

29:24.130 --> 29:25.696
[ Knock on door ]

29:25.698 --> 29:27.831
Estelle.

29:27.833 --> 29:29.666
Estelle.
Come on.

29:29.668 --> 29:31.235
Don't be that way.

29:31.237 --> 29:33.170
[ Knocking on door ]

29:33.172 --> 29:35.572
What are you doing here, Sean?

29:35.574 --> 29:40.144
I want you to tell me
what kind of fucked-up shit

29:40.146 --> 29:42.146
went down at the courtroom.

29:42.148 --> 29:45.048
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

29:45.050 --> 29:48.485
And I'd like you
to get off my porch.

29:48.487 --> 29:50.420
Letty pulled something.

29:50.422 --> 29:54.224
Sean, you need to get
off my porch.

29:54.226 --> 29:57.294
Fine.
Just let me see Jacob.

29:57.296 --> 29:59.229
[ Chuckling ] Absolutely not.

29:59.231 --> 30:02.666
He's my son.
Just get Jacob.

30:02.668 --> 30:05.969
You're not supposed to be here.

30:05.971 --> 30:10.340
I am supposed to be here.

30:10.342 --> 30:12.142
I'm supposed to be right here.

30:12.144 --> 30:13.243
I'm his father.

30:13.245 --> 30:14.344
I'm calling the cops.

30:14.346 --> 30:16.079
Put that phone down, you bitch.

30:16.081 --> 30:18.315
Shut your goddamn mouth!

30:18.317 --> 30:19.716
Or I'll shut it for you.

30:19.718 --> 30:21.351
He's my boy.

30:21.353 --> 30:24.521
I know.
And I'm sorry.

30:24.523 --> 30:28.425
But that is my wife and
that is my grandson inside,

30:28.427 --> 30:30.794
and you will treat them
with respect.

30:30.796 --> 30:32.362
I just want to see him.

30:32.364 --> 30:34.431
Is it summer?

30:34.433 --> 30:35.299
What?

30:35.301 --> 30:37.568
Is it a holiday?

30:37.570 --> 30:39.570
No.

30:39.572 --> 30:42.706
Then you don't get to see him.

30:42.708 --> 30:47.544
So you can leave right now,
or we can wait for the cops.

30:53.352 --> 30:54.718
Where's Letty?

30:54.720 --> 30:56.687
She ain't here.

30:56.689 --> 30:59.489
Yeah, figures.

30:59.491 --> 31:02.459
Whenever she does get here,

31:02.461 --> 31:05.696
you tell her I was here
for my son.

31:05.698 --> 31:09.066
I'll be back for him.

31:15.541 --> 31:17.641
It better be... Christmas.

31:17.643 --> 31:20.677
[ Car door closes,
engine starts ]

31:20.679 --> 31:23.747
♪♪

31:35.494 --> 31:37.094
What would you like?

31:37.096 --> 31:38.495
Everything.

31:38.497 --> 31:40.564
Hmm.

31:43.202 --> 31:44.601
Will this work?

31:44.603 --> 31:47.604
It's a start.

32:02.454 --> 32:04.588
Rough day?

32:07.493 --> 32:09.660
Well...

32:09.662 --> 32:11.662
I tried to stop
my hit man boyfriend

32:11.664 --> 32:14.765
from getting caught
at a hotel down the street

32:14.767 --> 32:16.166
in a sting I helped set up

32:16.168 --> 32:17.868
after cutting a deal
with the FBI

32:17.870 --> 32:20.103
so I could get my kid back.

32:20.873 --> 32:24.408
[ Rewinds ]

32:24.410 --> 32:26.143
Will this work?

32:26.145 --> 32:27.344
It's a start.

32:27.346 --> 32:29.446
[ Chuckles ]

32:32.184 --> 32:33.483
Rough day?

32:33.485 --> 32:37.654
Yeah. Wish I could
tell you about it.

32:37.656 --> 32:40.857
Well, it's kind of my job
for you to tell me about it.

32:40.859 --> 32:42.693
Not this.

32:42.695 --> 32:43.860
Okay.
- You strike me as someone

32:43.862 --> 32:45.829
who does just fine
on their own.

32:45.831 --> 32:46.830
Maybe.

32:46.832 --> 32:51.268
Should I be okay
with just fine?

32:51.270 --> 32:51.868
My experience?

32:51.870 --> 32:55.605
When you're with someone,
they always try to change you.

32:55.607 --> 32:57.874
And who wants to change,
really?

32:57.876 --> 33:00.544
I do.

33:00.546 --> 33:03.280
We're all just who we are,
I think.

33:03.282 --> 33:06.283
[ Chuckles ] But if there was
some magical person

33:06.285 --> 33:07.351
who could make us better,

33:07.353 --> 33:10.520
I mean, they would've
already done it, right?

33:55.768 --> 33:58.535
No, no.
Not here.

33:58.537 --> 34:01.371
- Sorry.
- Don't be.

34:01.373 --> 34:02.706
Happens all the time.

34:02.708 --> 34:05.842
Now what happens?

34:05.844 --> 34:08.745
We go upstairs.

34:09.515 --> 34:13.750
Three minutes,
then pay the bill.

34:13.752 --> 34:16.887
Then come to room 917.

34:17.990 --> 34:19.923
Room 917, three minutes.

34:19.925 --> 34:23.560
No. Three minutes,
then pay the bill.

34:23.562 --> 34:25.629
Then room 917.

35:16.381 --> 35:17.848
What the hell are you doing?

35:17.850 --> 35:18.782
I have to stop you.

35:18.784 --> 35:20.550
You don't have to do anything.

35:20.552 --> 35:22.719
[ Elevator buzzes ]

35:22.721 --> 35:23.487
Please!

35:23.489 --> 35:26.823
There's something
I have to tell you.

35:34.099 --> 35:37.334
I sold you out.

35:37.336 --> 35:38.869
To the FBI.

35:38.871 --> 35:40.937
The man you just met is
an undercover FBI agent,

35:40.939 --> 35:43.607
and there are at least two more
down there watching you.

35:43.609 --> 35:46.710
If you get out of this elevator
and go to that room,

35:46.712 --> 35:51.314
they will bust in two seconds
later and you'll be done.

35:52.751 --> 35:54.985
[ Scoffs ]

35:54.987 --> 35:56.086
What?

35:56.088 --> 35:58.188
Letty, I know you now.

35:58.190 --> 35:59.656
I know your lies.
The FBI?

35:59.658 --> 36:00.924
You're right,
I'm an amazing liar,

36:00.926 --> 36:02.926
but right now, I am
telling you the truth!

36:02.928 --> 36:05.195
Listen to me...
we're over, done.

36:05.197 --> 36:07.464
You need to leave me alone.

36:07.466 --> 36:11.368
How else do you think
I got Jacob?

36:14.940 --> 36:18.108
It was never gonna happen
in a million years,

36:18.110 --> 36:19.876
and now he's mine.

36:24.483 --> 36:25.715
I'm sorry.

36:25.717 --> 36:30.453
What was I supposed to do?

36:32.991 --> 36:35.425
So, let's just go.

36:35.427 --> 36:38.495
No.

36:38.497 --> 36:40.931
We are not good for each other.

36:40.933 --> 36:41.598
I know.

36:41.600 --> 36:45.635
You and Jacob are good
for each other.

36:45.637 --> 36:47.804
Maybe.

36:49.041 --> 36:52.309
[ Voice breaking ]
But I can't do it alone.

36:55.814 --> 36:57.914
You will have to.

36:58.083 --> 36:58.915
What are you doing?

36:58.917 --> 37:00.483
If you don't want to be with me,
that's fine,

37:00.485 --> 37:05.155
but please don't walk in there
and throw your life away.

37:05.157 --> 37:07.057
[ Elevator dings ]

37:13.498 --> 37:14.598
Please.

37:14.600 --> 37:17.567
Do not step off the elevator.

37:26.478 --> 37:33.650
♪ But I was burned
before the fire ♪

37:33.652 --> 37:34.551
♪ I'm burned up ♪

37:34.553 --> 37:40.757
♪ But I was burned
before the fire ♪

37:40.759 --> 37:42.826
♪ I'm burned up ♪

37:42.828 --> 37:44.995
[ Door opens ]

37:48.800 --> 37:50.834
You been here all night?

37:50.836 --> 37:53.737
Got in a couple of hours ago.

37:53.739 --> 37:55.238
Key wasn't under the plant.

37:55.240 --> 37:57.407
Yeah.
I took it back inside.

37:57.409 --> 37:59.376
I didn't want to risk
Sean finding it

37:59.378 --> 38:01.511
after he showed up yesterday.

38:01.513 --> 38:04.581
What?

38:04.583 --> 38:06.349
What did he want?

38:06.351 --> 38:09.519
What do you think?
Jacob.

38:09.521 --> 38:12.222
So you better take that boy
and disappear.

38:12.224 --> 38:14.357
But he can't just show up.

38:14.359 --> 38:16.426
When that man wants something,

38:16.428 --> 38:19.696
he always gets it eventually.

38:19.698 --> 38:22.332
So do I.

38:32.444 --> 38:34.177
- Hey, baby.
- Hi, mom.

38:34.179 --> 38:35.679
I'm sorry I had to leave.

38:35.681 --> 38:38.181
It's okay.
I'm used to it.

38:38.183 --> 38:42.218
Sean came here,
and he was really mad.

38:42.220 --> 38:43.887
Yeah.
I'm sure he was.

38:43.889 --> 38:47.590
But when I see him,
I want it to be fun, okay?

38:47.592 --> 38:50.226
For summer and the holidays.

38:50.228 --> 38:51.194
Every other holiday.

38:51.196 --> 38:53.730
Should we make a list
of all the holidays

38:53.732 --> 38:55.332
and choose which ones?

38:55.334 --> 38:57.434
Sure.

38:57.436 --> 39:01.471
But... otherwise,
you're gonna be with me.

39:01.473 --> 39:04.107
Where are we going?

39:16.621 --> 39:20.256
Are you sure you want
to take Jacob?

39:20.258 --> 39:21.691
No.

39:21.693 --> 39:25.395
Yes.
I don't know.

39:28.633 --> 39:31.501
If you're gonna raise a kid,

39:31.503 --> 39:33.303
you have to be totally selfless

39:33.305 --> 39:37.540
and that would be a good thing
for you to try on.

39:38.610 --> 39:39.943
He doesn't want to go with me.

39:39.945 --> 39:41.678
He doesn't know what he wants.

39:41.680 --> 39:44.848
Last week he wanted to be
a product tester

39:44.850 --> 39:46.516
at Piggly Wiggly.

39:46.518 --> 39:47.384
[ Chuckles ]

39:47.386 --> 39:48.651
It's your job to not care

39:48.653 --> 39:52.255
if what's right for him
isn't what he wants.

39:53.625 --> 39:56.559
I don't even know how to start.

39:56.561 --> 39:59.462
You just start.

39:59.464 --> 40:00.263
He wakes up.

40:00.265 --> 40:04.534
He can be a straight-up
little shit in the morning.

40:04.536 --> 40:05.935
It takes the will of the wolf

40:05.937 --> 40:07.937
to get that boy out of his bed.

40:07.939 --> 40:09.572
He's had all the vaccines.

40:09.574 --> 40:12.275
He's always coming home
with only one sock.

40:12.277 --> 40:14.944
Don't know how,
- But just always make sure

40:14.946 --> 40:16.346
you buy the exact same one

40:16.348 --> 40:17.814
so you can match
different pairs together

40:17.816 --> 40:19.783
because it's fucking annoying.

40:19.785 --> 40:22.252
He'll want different colors.

40:22.254 --> 40:23.653
Don't do it.
It's a trick.

40:23.655 --> 40:26.656
He gives his lunch away
if another kid is hungry,

40:26.658 --> 40:29.359
so always make sure
you pack him extra.

40:29.361 --> 40:31.394
He thinks he likes sushi,

40:31.396 --> 40:34.364
but he doesn't know what it is.

40:34.366 --> 40:38.468
[ Voice breaking ]
He needs time alone.

40:38.470 --> 40:40.303
Like you.

40:40.305 --> 40:44.741
So if you take him
to a party or whatever,

40:44.743 --> 40:46.943
just make sure you plan on that

40:46.945 --> 40:49.712
or else he just shuts down.

40:51.750 --> 40:56.286
Oh. He wet the bed
until two years ago.

40:56.288 --> 40:58.488
There haven't been
any relapses,

40:58.490 --> 41:01.691
but don't let your guard down
just yet.

41:03.061 --> 41:06.396
That should be enough
to get started.

41:08.500 --> 41:12.936
[ Sighs heavily ] Oh, my God.

41:12.938 --> 41:16.206
The rest is a lot harder
than that.

41:18.043 --> 41:21.377
But you can call me
if you want.

41:21.379 --> 41:23.346
[ Sniffles ]

41:24.516 --> 41:26.883
Jacob, it's time to go.

41:26.885 --> 41:30.353
Jacob:
I can't zip my backpack.

41:37.596 --> 41:39.062
♪ Lovin' you ♪

41:39.064 --> 41:44.000
♪ Isn't the right thing to do ♪

41:44.002 --> 41:45.702
I was hoping you'd be here.

41:45.704 --> 41:47.604
♪ How can I ♪
- I'm here.

41:47.606 --> 41:51.574
♪ Ever change things
that I feel? ♪
- So am I.

41:51.576 --> 41:53.276
What happened?

41:53.278 --> 41:55.778
We need to go right now.

41:55.780 --> 41:59.082
- Yeah.
- Oh, thank God.

41:59.084 --> 42:01.618
You found him.

42:01.620 --> 42:02.619
I did.

42:02.621 --> 42:04.621
♪ How can I ♪ You ready?

42:04.623 --> 42:06.723
♪ When you won't take it
from me? ♪

42:06.725 --> 42:09.025
I'll get the rest of my things.

42:09.027 --> 42:10.393
I'm gonna miss you, dude.

42:10.395 --> 42:11.828
Jacob: No, you're just never
gonna wear pants

42:11.830 --> 42:13.496
around the house again.
- Not true.

42:13.498 --> 42:14.864
I'll wear pants when it's cold.

42:14.866 --> 42:17.333
- Which one do you want?
- Which one what?

42:17.335 --> 42:19.602
- Which Range Rover?
- Are you serious?

42:19.604 --> 42:21.037
You said you wanted
a Range Rover Sport

42:21.039 --> 42:24.507
for Rob's Grasshoppers,
for the VIP-service aspect.

42:24.509 --> 42:26.075
I think I love you.

42:26.077 --> 42:27.443
I think I love you, too.

42:27.445 --> 42:29.746
Please, choose quickly.
Silver or black?

42:29.748 --> 42:31.714
Black.

42:31.716 --> 42:34.684
But black is hotter
in the summer.

42:34.686 --> 42:35.818
Plus, you got to wash it more

42:35.820 --> 42:37.654
'cause dirt shows
on black.
- Right. Silver.

42:37.656 --> 42:40.690
But black's a little bit
more VIP, right?

42:40.692 --> 42:43.426
- I don't know.
- Me neither.

42:43.428 --> 42:44.861
Please, we really have to go.

42:44.863 --> 42:47.330
Uh, just a sec.

42:53.705 --> 42:56.172
Don't be a jerk
to your mom, okay?

42:56.174 --> 42:58.575
Okay. Can I sit
in the front?

42:58.577 --> 42:59.042
Sure.

42:59.044 --> 43:00.743
As soon as Rob decides
which car he wants.

43:00.745 --> 43:02.712
It's between black and silver.

43:02.714 --> 43:05.081
- Yes, it is.
- There are pros and cons.

43:05.083 --> 43:05.882
Silver.

43:05.884 --> 43:09.352
- Why?
- Because I said silver.

43:10.488 --> 43:12.822
Yeah.
You're right.

43:12.824 --> 43:14.090
[ Chuckles ] Silver.

43:14.092 --> 43:19.862
♪ Baby, I'd give you my world ♪

43:20.665 --> 43:22.599
♪ Open up ♪

43:22.601 --> 43:28.504
♪ Everything's waiting
for you ♪

43:28.506 --> 43:34.043
♪ You can go your own way ♪

43:34.045 --> 43:37.547
♪ Go your own way ♪

43:37.549 --> 43:44.988
♪ You can call it
another lonely day ♪

43:46.191 --> 43:51.160
♪ You can go your own way ♪

43:51.162 --> 43:54.397
♪ Go your own way ♪

43:55.834 --> 43:57.634
Are you hungry?

43:57.636 --> 43:58.768
Not really.

43:58.770 --> 43:59.936
Yeah, me neither.

43:59.938 --> 44:01.971
I bet Mom's hungry.

44:01.973 --> 44:03.539
She's always hungry.

44:03.541 --> 44:05.908
But she doesn't know it
because she's sleeping.

44:05.910 --> 44:07.577
It's good for her to sleep.

44:07.579 --> 44:10.246
She drove all night.
Two nights in a row.

44:10.248 --> 44:12.448
- For you.
- Yeah.

44:12.450 --> 44:14.717
And for you.

44:16.121 --> 44:18.655
She's very special.

44:18.657 --> 44:20.523
<i>- Don't you...</i>
<i>- Yeah, she didn't want...</i>

44:20.525 --> 44:22.158
Judge Judy:
<i>Do you take medication?</i>

44:22.160 --> 44:24.260
[<i> Laughter</i> ]
<i>Do you take medication?</i>

44:24.262 --> 44:26.029
<i>- No, ma'am.</i>
<i>- You should.</i>

44:26.031 --> 44:28.931
<i>Because I've already</i>
<i>told you four times...</i>

44:28.933 --> 44:29.999
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

44:30.001 --> 44:33.569
<i>And when I start to speak,</i>
<i>understand that you came to me</i>

44:33.571 --> 44:36.072
<i>'cause something</i>
<i>was not working right.</i>

44:36.074 --> 44:37.740
Oh, shit.

44:37.742 --> 44:38.975
What?

44:38.977 --> 44:41.611
He got away.

44:44.716 --> 44:46.683
We'll find him.

44:49.688 --> 44:52.689
Your mom hasn't always
been there for you.

44:52.691 --> 44:54.691
I know.

44:54.693 --> 44:56.559
And you're choosing
to trust her.

44:56.561 --> 44:58.528
I'm proud of you for that.

44:58.530 --> 45:01.998
Do you trust her?

45:02.000 --> 45:03.199
I do trust her.

45:03.201 --> 45:05.501
Even though
she's not always honest?

45:05.503 --> 45:06.636
She is always honest.

45:06.638 --> 45:09.972
I don't mean with words.
Words are easy.

45:09.974 --> 45:11.040
Then what is she honest with?

45:11.042 --> 45:14.377
With her actions.
- The way she lives her life.

45:15.613 --> 45:18.848
Your genuine action
will explain itself

45:18.850 --> 45:21.951
and will explain your
other genuine actions.

45:21.953 --> 45:25.722
Your conformity
explains nothing.

45:25.724 --> 45:26.889
What?

45:26.891 --> 45:29.759
A guy named Ralph Waldo Emerson
wrote that.

45:29.761 --> 45:32.595
It reminds me of your mom.

45:33.631 --> 45:36.099
I think I am hungry.

45:38.903 --> 45:40.670
Yeah, me too.

45:41.639 --> 45:44.073
♪ You can go your own way ♪

45:44.075 --> 45:46.843
[ Siren wailing ]

45:46.845 --> 45:49.979
♪ Go your own way ♪
